strings:
<voice_0x01000BF3><se_low>Yangus: ...Wot's your game, eh? First ya grass on us
for somefin' we ain't done, and then ya come
an' 'elp us.

<voice_0x01000BF4><se_def>Angelo: Sorry if I've confused you. The people here have
a bit of a trust issue with me.

<voice_0x01000BF5><se_def>Angelo: I couldn't stick up for you before.
It would have backfired.

<voice_0x01000BF6><se_def>Angelo: The man who interrogated you, Marcello...
He hates me.
<voice_0x01000BF7><se_def>Angelo: That's why I had to let him put you in the cells before I could help you.
<voice_0x01000BF8><se_low>Yangus: That's all well an' good, but ya still don't know us from Adam.
<voice_0x01000BF9><se_low>Yangus: Ain't you worried about us bein' friends wiv this old monster, eh? Yer just 'appy to let us go, are ya?

<voice_0x01000BFA><se_def>Angelo: True, I don't know anything about you.
And I wasn't there when you were caught.
But I do know you saved the Abbot's life.
<voice_0x01000BFB><se_def>Angelo: Because just before you were brought to the interrogation room, the sinister feeling that's been lingering in the air went away.

<voice_0x01000BFC><se_def>Angelo: I must thank you for that.
I'm not so ruthless that I'd hang you out to dry.

<voice_0x01000BFD><se_def>Angelo: And besides, I couldn't stand by while there was
a lady in trouble. Marcello's a rather talented inquisitor, you know.
